Center: Russian Nuclear Structure and Reaction Data Centre, Kurchatov Institute, Moscow, Russia
title: Integral Excitation Functions of Alpha-Induced Reactions On Titanium,Iron and Nickel.

x4freetext: FOR THE 3 TARGET ELEMENTS INDIVIDUAL IRRADIATION
EXPERIMENTS WERE PERFORMED.  FOR EACH OF THEM TWO TYPES
OF STACKS WERE USED IN ORDER TO AVOID TO LARGE ERRORSIN
THE  PARTICLE  ENERGIES  DUE  TO  THE  EFFECT  OF RANGE
STRAGGLING.   THE  FIRST  ONE  HAD   TO   DEGRADE   THE
ALPHA-ENERGY  FROM  172.5  MEV  TO ABOUT 80 MEV AND THE
SECOND ONE FROM 90 MEV TO ABOUT  15  MEV.   EACH  STACK
CONSISTED  OF  A  NUMBER  OF  HIGH  PURITY TARGET FOILS
/THICKNESS 25 MUMETERS FOR TI AND FE  AND  50  MUMETERS
FOR  NI/,  ALTERNATELY  FOLLOWED  BY  A  HIGH PURITY 25
MUMETERS AL CATCHER FOIL AND  BY  COMMERCIAL  GRADE  AL
DEGRADER  FOILS.   IN FRONT OF EACH STACK, ADDITIONALLY
100 MU METERS AL-FOIL WAS PLACED FOR FLUX MONITOR.
